noise-suppression-for-voice (1.10+ds-0deepin1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging for noise-suppression-for-voice 1.10+ds

  * LADSPA-only build of real-time noise suppression plugin based on
  * Xiph's RNNoise library.

  * Packaging highlights:
      - Exclude JUCE/FST/catch2/toolchains via Files-Excluded (ds repack)
      - Use system Catch2 v3: find_package(Catch2 3 CONFIG REQUIRED)
      - Migrate test headers from Catch2 v2 to v3 API
      - Install to /usr/lib/ladspa/ per LADSPA convention
      - Full hardening (+all) and LTO (+lto) enabled
      - 3/3 tests pass, lintian --pedantic clean

